1
00:00:05,040 --> 00:00:10,670
[English subtitles are available.]

2
00:00:11,070 --> 00:00:13,010
[Ji Chang-wook]

3
00:00:15,880 --> 00:00:17,210
[Kim You-jung]

4
00:00:22,790 --> 00:00:24,890
[Backstreet Rookie]

5
00:00:28,260 --> 00:00:29,330
Saet-byul,

6
00:00:29,860 --> 00:00:31,090
I would like to be

7
00:00:31,930 --> 00:00:34,130
someone special to you, too.

8
00:00:38,330 --> 00:00:39,470
Will you accept my red tulips?

9
00:00:54,620 --> 00:00:55,790
Mr. Choi,

10
00:00:58,820 --> 00:01:00,460
I'll answer that

11
00:01:01,520 --> 00:01:02,960
later.

12
00:01:10,030 --> 00:01:12,270
I'm not dreaming to become someone
as great as you are,

13
00:01:12,340 --> 00:01:14,600
but I want to achieve something
on my own, too.

14
00:01:16,210 --> 00:01:19,840
I'll answer you when I pass the GED.

15
00:01:29,289 --> 00:01:33,460
Sure. You've waited for me all along,

16
00:01:34,560 --> 00:01:36,190
so I'll wait for you this time.

17
00:01:39,330 --> 00:01:43,330
Saet-byul, don't you ever feel
like you've achieved nothing.

18
00:01:44,930 --> 00:01:48,470
You're responsible, loyal,
a great fighter...

19
00:01:48,640 --> 00:01:51,509
And you're diligent.

20
00:01:51,570 --> 00:01:53,080
That's why the head office

21
00:01:53,140 --> 00:01:56,410
is naming you as the assistant manager
of the store.

22
00:01:59,550 --> 00:02:02,620
Saet-byul, you are already enough.

23
00:02:03,520 --> 00:02:04,590
You're awesome.

24
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:09,860
Thank you, Mr. Choi.

25
00:02:10,259 --> 00:02:11,460
It's nothing.

26
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:17,270
How did you prepare all of this?

27
00:02:18,130 --> 00:02:19,340
It's beautiful here.

28
00:02:20,370 --> 00:02:22,110
Did you prepare wine or anything?

29
00:02:22,640 --> 00:02:24,640
What wine?

30
00:02:24,710 --> 00:02:27,480
People usually drink wine
when they come to places like this.

31
00:02:27,540 --> 00:02:29,750
-What wine?
-Maybe I've watched too many dramas.

32
00:02:29,810 --> 00:02:33,480
You mean something like this?

33
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:35,450
Is this what you want?

34
00:02:41,590 --> 00:02:44,730
You drink. I'll go and plant the tulips.

35
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:48,460
[You lost.]

36
00:02:48,530 --> 00:02:50,500
-I lost again.
[-Freshen up!]

37
00:02:51,070 --> 00:02:52,140
[Give it to me.]

38
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:53,540
Welcome.

39
00:02:55,610 --> 00:02:56,840
Yong-pil.

40
00:03:10,390 --> 00:03:13,460
Jang-mi, how did you get here?

41
00:03:13,590 --> 00:03:18,030
I thought of how you said that you run
a convenience store in Shinseong-dong.

42
00:03:18,329 --> 00:03:22,170
I also have to ask you a favor
before I go to China tomorrow.

43
00:03:22,470 --> 00:03:23,930
What favor?

44
00:03:24,070 --> 00:03:27,170
Don't you think it'd be possible
to find Boon-hee

45
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:28,840
if you look
into Busan alumni associations?

46
00:03:30,410 --> 00:03:33,110
Boon-hee again?
You have to forget about her.

47
00:03:33,180 --> 00:03:34,780
How can I?

48
00:03:35,810 --> 00:03:37,680
Boon-hee is the person I missed the most

49
00:03:37,810 --> 00:03:40,020
ever since leaving Korea.

50
00:03:40,950 --> 00:03:44,090
Jang-mi, I really don't know
what Boon-hee is doing.

51
00:03:44,350 --> 00:03:48,090
I haven't seen Gong Boon-hee for 40 years!

52
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:51,630
Dad!

53
00:03:55,870 --> 00:03:58,170
Why are you saying that you don't know...

54
00:04:01,770 --> 00:04:02,740
You're here.

55
00:04:03,110 --> 00:04:04,810
Is that your son, Yong-pil?

56
00:04:05,010 --> 00:04:06,410
He's handsome.

57
00:04:07,180 --> 00:04:08,980
Hello.

58
00:04:09,780 --> 00:04:12,880
How do you know my dad?

59
00:04:12,980 --> 00:04:16,350
We were friends in high school.
My name is Hong Jang-mi.

60
00:04:16,490 --> 00:04:17,950
Hello.

61
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:23,730
♫ Alone in the audience ♫

62
00:04:23,790 --> 00:04:25,630
Jang-mi, I love you.

63
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:34,200
Look at the time.

64
00:04:34,270 --> 00:04:36,740
Jang-mi, come here.

65
00:04:44,280 --> 00:04:47,920
I need to talk to my son about something
very important.

66
00:04:48,250 --> 00:04:49,090
Is that so?

67
00:04:49,150 --> 00:04:52,320
Yes. I'll call you right away
if I ever hear from Boon-hee,

68
00:04:52,390 --> 00:04:54,460
so just wait for my call in China,
all right?

69
00:04:54,520 --> 00:04:56,659
-I think I should stay until I meet...
-Go.

70
00:04:58,430 --> 00:05:00,600
Go! You can go now. Bye.

71
00:05:00,660 --> 00:05:01,830
-Go.
-Fine.

72
00:05:05,100 --> 00:05:06,370
Gosh.

73
00:05:07,900 --> 00:05:10,840
Dad! I know she's your first love,

74
00:05:10,910 --> 00:05:13,110
but how could you say
that you don't know Mom?

75
00:05:13,940 --> 00:05:17,180
It's all a misunderstanding.
It's a long story.

76
00:05:17,250 --> 00:05:20,550
Dad, no story can ever justify that. Ever!

77
00:05:20,620 --> 00:05:23,590
Jang-mi used to be best friends
with Boon-hee,

78
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:26,490
but Boon-hee doesn't want to see her!

79
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:29,190
Why? Why wouldn't Mom want to see her?

80
00:05:29,260 --> 00:05:30,360
Look.

81
00:05:31,090 --> 00:05:33,760
I'm Boon-hee's first love,

82
00:05:31,130 --> 00:05:33,000
[Boon-hee]

83
00:05:33,060 --> 00:05:35,230
[First love, me]

84
00:05:34,159 --> 00:05:36,900
while Jang-mi was mine.

85
00:05:35,300 --> 00:05:38,430
[First love, Jang-mi]

86
00:05:37,100 --> 00:05:39,570
Boon-hee and Jang-mi were friends.

87
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:40,140
[Best friends]

88
00:05:39,640 --> 00:05:41,640
If you were Mom,
would you want to see Jang-mi?

89
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:41,540
[Jang-mi, Boon-hee]

90
00:05:42,770 --> 00:05:44,370
My goodness.

91
00:05:46,610 --> 00:05:49,710
My best friend disappeared

92
00:05:49,780 --> 00:05:51,110
without leaving a single letter.

93
00:05:51,580 --> 00:05:53,080
You must miss her.

94
00:05:53,150 --> 00:05:57,090
As if. That wench.
I already erased her from my head.

95
00:05:57,750 --> 00:06:01,190
Is that the best friend who left

96
00:06:01,260 --> 00:06:04,660
without leaving a single note
for Mrs. Gong?

97
00:06:04,730 --> 00:06:07,000
Saet-byul, how do you know about her?

98
00:06:07,060 --> 00:06:10,470
Mrs. Gong told me about her

99
00:06:10,830 --> 00:06:12,800
and how she never wants to see her again.

100
00:06:13,700 --> 00:06:15,070
See? I told you!

101
00:06:15,140 --> 00:06:18,640
Don't you ever tell Mom
that Jang-mi is in Korea, okay?

102
00:06:18,710 --> 00:06:19,910
Dad!

103
00:06:20,110 --> 00:06:22,610
Take over my shift. My back hurts.

104
00:06:22,780 --> 00:06:26,680
No, you can watch the store
the whole night.

105
00:06:27,250 --> 00:06:28,220
Let's go, Saet-byul.

106
00:06:28,320 --> 00:06:30,850
Mr. Choi, I think...

107
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:33,659
I think you should tell her...

108
00:06:36,860 --> 00:06:39,260
Why is everyone always on Boon-hee's side?

109
00:06:41,260 --> 00:06:43,030
What did I ever do wrong?

110
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:03,220
-Mom.
-We're home.

111
00:07:03,290 --> 00:07:04,320
Hey.

112
00:07:04,990 --> 00:07:06,920
Why are you two coming together?
What about the store?

113
00:07:06,990 --> 00:07:09,160
Dad is going to watch it overnight.

114
00:07:09,590 --> 00:07:13,460
He has been avoiding me lately.
Did he do something wrong?

115
00:07:13,530 --> 00:07:17,030
No, nothing. What are you up to?

116
00:07:17,100 --> 00:07:19,840
I heard that taking a foot bath is

117
00:07:19,900 --> 00:07:22,540
the best thing to do to get
foot-swelling go away.

118
00:07:22,940 --> 00:07:24,440
You could just buy a foot bath machine.

119
00:07:24,510 --> 00:07:28,380
A foot bath machine? We're still paying
the installments for Dad's massage chair!

120
00:07:28,440 --> 00:07:31,650
Foot baths easily cost 200,000 won.
We can't afford one.

121
00:07:33,280 --> 00:07:36,920
Actually, I think what you've got is
quite decent. It even massages.

122
00:07:36,990 --> 00:07:39,190
Massage? It doesn't.

123
00:07:39,260 --> 00:07:41,720
Of course it does, Mom.

124
00:07:41,790 --> 00:07:44,090
See? Give me your foot. Like this.

125
00:07:47,460 --> 00:07:48,870
I'll massage your shoulders.

126
00:07:48,930 --> 00:07:50,900
-What?
-You're so tense up here.

127
00:07:50,970 --> 00:07:54,670
What a luxurious day I'm having today.

128
00:07:54,740 --> 00:07:56,440
Is this my lucky day or something?

129
00:07:57,440 --> 00:08:00,710
I couldn't decide on what to get you
with my first pay as an advisor,

130
00:08:00,780 --> 00:08:02,250
but now I know. I'll get you a foot bath.

131
00:08:02,310 --> 00:08:05,180
-Really?
-Yes. Some shoes as well.

132
00:08:05,250 --> 00:08:07,020
No, you can't buy me shoes.

133
00:08:07,080 --> 00:08:09,090
I might run away if you do.

134
00:08:09,520 --> 00:08:12,520
I'll buy you shoes when I get my first pay
as the assistant manager.

135
00:08:12,590 --> 00:08:14,660
What? You're going to be
an assistant manager?

136
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:16,460
I've handed the ownership of the store
to the headquarters.

137
00:08:16,530 --> 00:08:18,690
They offered to promote Saet-byul
as the assistant manager.

138
00:08:18,760 --> 00:08:20,760
Really? That happened?

139
00:08:20,830 --> 00:08:24,130
That's amazing! That's great news.

140
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:26,170
Congratulations, Saet-byul.

141
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:29,640
-Thank you.
-That's awesome.

142
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:33,710
Goodness.

143
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:38,409
What a great man Mr. Choi is.

144
00:08:40,150 --> 00:08:41,919
He's a perfect son.

145
00:08:43,750 --> 00:08:45,660
And a perfect man.

146
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:55,100
I would like to be

147
00:08:56,530 --> 00:08:59,070
someone special to you, too.

148
00:09:01,270 --> 00:09:02,370
Will you accept my red tulips?

149
00:09:06,740 --> 00:09:08,910
[I've been dreaming
about that moment forever.]

150
00:09:10,010 --> 00:09:11,880
[Why couldn't I answer him right away?]

151
00:09:13,250 --> 00:09:14,680
[I took]

152
00:09:14,750 --> 00:09:18,150
[slow steps toward Mr. Choi,
one step at a time,]

153
00:09:20,460 --> 00:09:22,290
[and I've reached my goal now.]

154
00:09:23,760 --> 00:09:24,830
[So, why?]

155
00:09:26,660 --> 00:09:28,800
[Why do I feel as scared about this
as I am happy about it?]

156
00:09:40,040 --> 00:09:42,780
[Aren't you hungry? I'm going to have
some ramyeon.]

157
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:51,490
-Gosh, you startled me.
-Saet-byul.

158
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:53,120
I'll make you some good ramyeon.

159
00:09:55,690 --> 00:09:57,090
Why are you two coming out from there
at the same time?

160
00:09:57,260 --> 00:09:59,100
-I'm getting some water.
-I'm going to the bathroom.

161
00:09:59,160 --> 00:10:00,100
I see.

162
00:10:04,030 --> 00:10:05,530
[When Mom heads back to her room,]

163
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:08,240
[I'll make you some delicious ramyeon
with an egg on top.]

164
00:10:08,300 --> 00:10:09,810
[Great. Make sure to pop the yolk.]

165
00:10:09,870 --> 00:10:12,910
[Pop the yolk?
It's so much better when it's not popped.]

166
00:10:12,980 --> 00:10:14,310
What are you two doing?

167
00:10:12,980 --> 00:10:14,240
[Make the noodles chewy.]

168
00:10:16,350 --> 00:10:18,580
-Are you two dancing?
-Yes.

169
00:10:18,710 --> 00:10:19,920
-We're dancing.
-Yes.

170
00:10:21,150 --> 00:10:24,820
Look at that. You got
the beautiful dance lines from me.

171
00:10:24,990 --> 00:10:28,060
Saet-byul, when I was young,
I was quite the dancer.

172
00:10:28,490 --> 00:10:35,100
♫ When will you and I meet ♫

173
00:10:35,160 --> 00:10:36,370
Dance, Saet-byul!

174
00:10:36,830 --> 00:10:40,970
♫ And make history ♫

175
00:10:41,040 --> 00:10:42,740
I'm a great dancer myself.

176
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:44,710
Look at that.

177
00:10:45,070 --> 00:10:46,510
Mrs. Gong, aren't you going to sleep?

178
00:10:46,580 --> 00:10:49,780
I'm feeling perfectly rejuvenated

179
00:10:49,850 --> 00:10:51,250
after that shoulder massage you gave me!

180
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:54,480
But you have work early morning tomorrow.

181
00:10:54,550 --> 00:10:56,820
You should sleep.

182
00:10:56,890 --> 00:10:58,720
Why? Are you two going to do something
after I sleep?

183
00:11:02,060 --> 00:11:03,660
-We're going to sleep.
-We have to sleep, too.

184
00:11:03,730 --> 00:11:04,990
-Of course you have to.
-Yes, we do.

185
00:11:05,060 --> 00:11:07,030
You should go sleep.
I'm going to watch some more TV.

186
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:09,330
What? Okay, I'm going to bed now.

187
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:11,200
-Goodnight!
-Goodnight.

188
00:11:11,270 --> 00:11:13,170
Goodnight! And come out if you get bored.

189
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:19,010
-Sure.
-♫ Love doesn't come easy ♫

190
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:23,710
♫ Not everyone can fall in love ♫

191
00:11:24,210 --> 00:11:25,280
Hold up.

192
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:31,850
[We need to come up with signs.]

193
00:11:32,620 --> 00:11:33,660
"Signs"?

194
00:11:35,220 --> 00:11:36,430
[What signs?]

195
00:11:36,730 --> 00:11:38,360
[Just to be safe.]

196
00:11:38,490 --> 00:11:39,800
[What's your favorite fruit?]

197
00:11:41,830 --> 00:11:42,900
[Grapes!]

198
00:11:44,170 --> 00:11:45,740
[Grapes]

199
00:11:46,840 --> 00:11:48,970
[Okay, then. From now on, "Grapes" mean
"Let's meet."]

200
00:11:54,680 --> 00:11:55,680
[What?]

201
00:11:57,150 --> 00:11:59,880
[And "Strawberry" means "No."
Is that okay?]

202
00:12:00,650 --> 00:12:02,520
[Strawberry]

203
00:12:03,420 --> 00:12:05,690
[What a kid you are.]

204
00:12:10,560 --> 00:12:12,460
[These are our signs, okay?]

205
00:12:13,030 --> 00:12:14,100
[Strawberry!]

206
00:12:14,630 --> 00:12:16,100
[I'm going to go to sleep now.]

207
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:20,100
[Goodnight. Grapes tomorrow.]

208
00:12:22,170 --> 00:12:23,170
Grapes.

209
00:12:24,510 --> 00:12:26,880
He's so cute. Grapes!

210
00:12:27,940 --> 00:12:30,180
Grapes! Goodnight.

211
00:12:37,890 --> 00:12:39,960
Grapes? Grapes.

212
00:12:44,030 --> 00:12:45,230
This is adorable!

213
00:12:50,930 --> 00:12:54,300
[Franchise contract, GS Retail]

214
00:12:51,830 --> 00:12:54,300
This is the franchise contract.
Take a look.

215
00:12:54,370 --> 00:12:55,970
[Franchise contract, GS Retail]

216
00:12:56,070 --> 00:13:00,240
Mom, this part is about the opening date
of the store.

217
00:13:01,140 --> 00:13:03,980
The hours of operation are stated
right here.

218
00:13:04,380 --> 00:13:05,480
Here.

219
00:13:06,380 --> 00:13:07,520
-Hold on.
-Okay.

220
00:13:09,320 --> 00:13:10,350
Hey, Seong-tae.

221
00:13:10,890 --> 00:13:12,860
What? The Jangchung-dong branch?

222
00:13:12,920 --> 00:13:14,120
I'm...

223
00:13:16,260 --> 00:13:17,460
I'm busy with something.

224
00:13:17,860 --> 00:13:20,260
All right, then.

225
00:13:23,570 --> 00:13:27,040
Mom, I have to get going.
Something urgent came up.

226
00:13:27,100 --> 00:13:28,570
-You're leaving?
-Yes.

227
00:13:28,640 --> 00:13:30,670
I've looked over the contract,

228
00:13:30,740 --> 00:13:34,580
and Director Yoo here will explain
the rest to you.

229
00:13:34,710 --> 00:13:36,150
Don't worry, you can go.

230
00:13:36,310 --> 00:13:38,180
Mrs. Gong and I will
take care of the rest.

231
00:13:38,250 --> 00:13:39,750
Sorry about that.

232
00:13:40,750 --> 00:13:41,950
Okay, then.

233
00:13:43,850 --> 00:13:46,460
Assistant Manager Jung,
have a great shift.

234
00:13:47,790 --> 00:13:49,590
See you later, Advisor Choi.

235
00:13:50,190 --> 00:13:52,190
-I'll be back soon.
-Come back quick.

236
00:13:54,130 --> 00:13:56,230
Grapes!

237
00:13:58,400 --> 00:14:00,200
Grapes? What?

238
00:14:01,440 --> 00:14:02,770
I was wondering

239
00:14:03,270 --> 00:14:05,440
how Dae-hyun has been at work.

240
00:14:05,510 --> 00:14:09,210
I hear that he has
a lot of responsibilities.

241
00:14:10,210 --> 00:14:11,950
The head office has a lot of regrets.

242
00:14:12,950 --> 00:14:15,680
We regret not recognizing
such a great man earlier.

243
00:14:16,720 --> 00:14:17,990
You scared me.

244
00:14:18,520 --> 00:14:21,860
My goodness!

245
00:14:23,330 --> 00:14:25,730
I didn't know you could joke like that.

246
00:14:25,790 --> 00:14:27,900
You scared me for a moment.

247
00:14:28,330 --> 00:14:31,100
And this is for you.

248
00:14:32,940 --> 00:14:34,040
Here.

249
00:14:39,110 --> 00:14:40,140
Look at that!

250
00:14:43,180 --> 00:14:44,350
My goodness.

251
00:14:45,080 --> 00:14:46,620
Will you look at that?

252
00:14:46,680 --> 00:14:49,120
Isn't this crocodile leather?

253
00:14:49,290 --> 00:14:50,420
Do you like it?

254
00:14:50,490 --> 00:14:53,390
Of course I do!

255
00:14:54,420 --> 00:14:57,360
This costs 400,000 won at least, no?

256
00:14:57,590 --> 00:15:00,330
You've spent quite a bit of money.

257
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:01,900
Or is it 500,000 won?

258
00:15:01,960 --> 00:15:05,130
-No, it's...
-Was it 300,000 won? Let's hear it.

259
00:15:05,330 --> 00:15:07,800
You've spent so much money.

260
00:15:07,870 --> 00:15:09,140
This bag must be so expensive.

261
