508
00:29:43,910 --> 00:29:47,380
If you happen to reach her,
could you give this for me?

509
00:29:48,750 --> 00:29:50,290
I don't think I'll ever come back.

510
00:30:00,700 --> 00:30:01,760
-Dad.
-What?

511
00:30:02,300 --> 00:30:04,100
-Mom.
-Your mother?

512
00:30:04,170 --> 00:30:05,870
-What do we do?
-To the storage room!

513
00:30:05,930 --> 00:30:08,240
You send her back home. You, come with me.

514
00:30:08,300 --> 00:30:09,640
Come here. It's okay. Come here.

515
00:30:09,700 --> 00:30:11,140
-Where are we going?
-Come here.

516
00:30:11,210 --> 00:30:13,110
-Why are we going inside?
-Go inside.

517
00:30:13,680 --> 00:30:16,180
What's wrong? Did something happen?

518
00:30:16,580 --> 00:30:17,950
Well...

519
00:30:19,480 --> 00:30:22,480
-What is it?
-My wife is here.

520
00:30:22,550 --> 00:30:24,050
Then, let me say hello to her.

521
00:30:24,520 --> 00:30:26,420
No. It's better that you don't.

522
00:30:26,550 --> 00:30:28,990
She'll leave soon.

523
00:30:29,220 --> 00:30:30,790
But why are you so nervous?

524
00:30:32,360 --> 00:30:34,860
I don't know. I have no idea.

525
00:30:35,360 --> 00:30:36,500
My gosh, that awful woman.

526
00:30:36,560 --> 00:30:38,130
-Ma'am.
-Hey, Mom.

527
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:40,100
What? Why are you back so early?

528
00:30:40,170 --> 00:30:41,900
Did Yong-pil take off already?

529
00:30:42,400 --> 00:30:44,140
-Yes, he left.
-Yes.

530
00:30:44,210 --> 00:30:45,370
He left?

531
00:30:46,040 --> 00:30:48,310
That sly jerk. That's all right. Fine.

532
00:30:48,540 --> 00:30:51,480
I wanted to clean the place
with or without him today.

533
00:30:51,550 --> 00:30:52,750
Let's start with the storage room.

534
00:30:52,810 --> 00:30:53,620
-No!
-No!

535
00:30:53,680 --> 00:30:55,320
You startled me. What's wrong with you?

536
00:30:55,380 --> 00:30:57,190
Just because.
We can clean the storage room later.

537
00:30:57,250 --> 00:30:59,420
-We should do it. It's too much for you.
-Right.

538
00:30:59,490 --> 00:31:01,790
Mom. Oh, right.
You should go see your client.

539
00:31:01,860 --> 00:31:02,820
You brat.

540
00:31:02,890 --> 00:31:05,490
What client? I just lost my client.

541
00:31:05,560 --> 00:31:07,030
Move out of my way. I'll--

542
00:31:07,100 --> 00:31:08,330
-No, Mom.
-Are you mad?

543
00:31:08,400 --> 00:31:10,100
Why do you keep stopping me?

544
00:31:10,160 --> 00:31:12,230
-What is it? What's wrong with you?
-My gosh.

545
00:31:12,300 --> 00:31:13,540
Want a hug or a piggyback ride?

546
00:31:13,600 --> 00:31:15,300
-What's wrong with you?
-Ma'am!

547
00:31:15,370 --> 00:31:17,310
What's wrong?
What's gotten into you, Saet-byul?

548
00:31:17,370 --> 00:31:18,670
-Mom.
-Move out of my way.

549
00:31:18,740 --> 00:31:20,210
-No, I...
-Ma'am.

550
00:31:21,180 --> 00:31:23,280
There's no need to come in here.
I finished cleaning.

551
00:31:23,340 --> 00:31:26,680
I thought you already left.
What a surprise you're still here.

552
00:31:26,750 --> 00:31:29,720
You should go home and rest up.
I'll take care of the rest.

553
00:31:29,780 --> 00:31:31,590
-What?
-You're the best. All right.

554
00:31:31,650 --> 00:31:33,220
I see. You finished cleaning there?

555
00:31:33,290 --> 00:31:36,220
If you're done in there,
let's clean the windows over there.

556
00:31:36,290 --> 00:31:38,090
-Let's go.
-I'm all right.

557
00:31:38,160 --> 00:31:39,730
What? Go and clean the windows.

558
00:31:39,790 --> 00:31:41,760
Let's go and clean the windows.

559
00:31:41,830 --> 00:31:42,900
-Okay.
-Let's clean them.

560
00:31:42,960 --> 00:31:44,900
-The windows.
-You clean the windows.

561
00:31:46,330 --> 00:31:48,740
What is it?
Are you hiding a baby in there?

562
00:31:48,800 --> 00:31:50,240
What are you trying to eat without me?

563
00:31:50,310 --> 00:31:51,940
If it's something good, you're dead meat.

564
00:31:52,010 --> 00:31:53,580
Let's see. What do you have here?

565
00:31:54,210 --> 00:31:55,410
You're dead meat. What...

566
00:32:06,390 --> 00:32:07,420
Who are you?

567
00:32:08,160 --> 00:32:12,130
My gosh. Oh, no. This is bad. Goodness.

568
00:32:16,760 --> 00:32:18,700
[Backstreet Rookie]

569
00:32:21,700 --> 00:32:22,940
Hello.

570
00:32:23,240 --> 00:32:26,170
I'm Choi Yong-pil's friend.
My name is Hong Jang-mi.

571
00:32:31,150 --> 00:32:32,110
Jang-mi?

572
00:32:33,210 --> 00:32:35,850
My dear, let me explain.

573
00:32:36,780 --> 00:32:38,190
Please listen.

574
00:32:41,760 --> 00:32:45,030
Aren't you Gong Boon-hee?

575
00:32:45,960 --> 00:32:47,430
Aren't you Boon-hee?

576
00:32:48,900 --> 00:32:50,800
My gosh.

577
00:32:51,170 --> 00:32:52,670
Darn it.

578
00:32:54,140 --> 00:32:56,000
Did you two get married?

579
00:32:58,410 --> 00:33:01,240
Why did you say you didn't know...

580
00:33:04,180 --> 00:33:06,810
Did he say that
he didn't know he married me?

581
00:33:07,020 --> 00:33:08,820
-A few days ago,
-Okay.

582
00:33:08,880 --> 00:33:10,280
I came back to Korea from China.

583
00:33:10,690 --> 00:33:13,050
When I asked him about you,
he said he didn't know where you were.

584
00:33:13,250 --> 00:33:15,920
I see. You got here a few days ago
and met with him?

585
00:33:16,160 --> 00:33:18,330
Did you meet him

586
00:33:20,500 --> 00:33:22,600
at the cafe in a hotel?

587
00:33:23,230 --> 00:33:24,370
That's right.

588
00:33:27,400 --> 00:33:29,140
I heard you moved to China.

589
00:33:30,910 --> 00:33:32,040
Where do you live?

590
00:33:34,580 --> 00:33:35,580
Don't tell her.

591
00:33:36,880 --> 00:33:38,080
Zhangjiajie.

592
00:33:42,750 --> 00:33:45,190
I see. You live in Zhangjiajie.

593
00:33:47,620 --> 00:33:49,290
I didn't know
Jang-mi lived in Zhangjiajie.

594
00:33:53,090 --> 00:33:54,860
-Boon-hee.
-What?

595
00:33:55,900 --> 00:33:57,170
It's been so long.

596
00:33:58,930 --> 00:34:00,000
Jang-mi.

597
00:34:01,270 --> 00:34:02,200
Yes?

598
00:34:10,340 --> 00:34:11,350
I never

599
00:34:12,850 --> 00:34:15,380
met you today.

600
00:34:15,820 --> 00:34:16,949
Let's say we never met.

601
00:34:19,790 --> 00:34:20,860
Honey.

602
00:34:21,159 --> 00:34:23,560
Excuse me. Could you move out of my way?

603
00:34:25,830 --> 00:34:26,889
Honey.

604
00:34:35,170 --> 00:34:36,270
My dear.

605
00:34:43,409 --> 00:34:44,449
Boon-hee.

606
00:35:01,600 --> 00:35:02,660
Gosh.

607
00:35:04,570 --> 00:35:06,930
Darn it. Oh, no.

608
00:35:07,900 --> 00:35:09,700
What do I do? I'm in big trouble.

609
00:35:10,610 --> 00:35:12,470
Gosh. Darn it!

610
00:35:13,040 --> 00:35:15,040
[Tented Bar]

611
00:35:24,590 --> 00:35:29,390
At times like this,
I should turn off my phone.

612
00:35:30,390 --> 00:35:32,360
But I'm worried my clients might call.

613
00:35:33,260 --> 00:35:38,100
How pathetic that I can't even turn off
my phone whenever I want.

614
00:35:49,080 --> 00:35:50,040
Hello?

615
00:35:50,650 --> 00:35:52,810
Ma'am, it's me. It's Yeon-joo.

616
00:35:53,480 --> 00:35:56,650
Hey. Why are you calling me at this hour?

617
00:35:57,850 --> 00:36:00,450
I called you to let you know
that the contract has been finalized.

618
00:36:00,860 --> 00:36:02,260
We'll wire the money next week.

619
00:36:02,590 --> 00:36:05,090
I see. You could have called Dae-hyun.

620
00:36:05,160 --> 00:36:07,500
Okay. Thank you.

621
00:36:07,560 --> 00:36:08,530
Bye.

622
00:36:08,800 --> 00:36:11,070
[Hey, I want one more bottle of soju.]

623
00:36:11,200 --> 00:36:12,370
Ma'am.

624
00:36:14,270 --> 00:36:15,270
Hello?

625
00:36:15,340 --> 00:36:17,940
I want to drink soju with you too.

626
00:36:18,370 --> 00:36:19,410
What?

627
00:36:19,470 --> 00:36:22,780
I'm off work now.
I'm passing through Shinseong-dong.

628
00:36:22,840 --> 00:36:24,050
Just one drink, please?

629
00:36:24,410 --> 00:36:28,620
You wouldn't like
to drink at a place like this.

630
00:36:29,120 --> 00:36:30,280
Where are you?

631
00:36:30,350 --> 00:36:32,320
I'll tell you what I think
after I see it for myself.

632
00:36:35,990 --> 00:36:37,830
-All right.
-Will Mrs. Gong be all right?

633
00:36:37,890 --> 00:36:39,390
She won't answer our calls.

634
00:36:39,860 --> 00:36:42,260
My dad has broken her heart
so many times before.

635
00:36:43,030 --> 00:36:45,530
But my dad crossed the line today,
didn't he?

636
00:36:46,170 --> 00:36:48,540
Saet-byul, don't worry.
She'll be home soon.

637
00:36:51,770 --> 00:36:53,210
-This looks good.
-Try it.

638
00:37:00,950 --> 00:37:03,280
It tastes good, right?

639
00:37:03,520 --> 00:37:05,550
See? I told you
I cook great instant noodles.

640
00:37:05,650 --> 00:37:06,550
You have my approval.

641
00:37:06,650 --> 00:37:09,790
Tomorrow, I'll buy you
something even more delicious.

642
00:37:13,330 --> 00:37:16,330
Saet-byul, now that
I'm about to hand over my store,

643
00:37:16,400 --> 00:37:17,900
it feels a little weird.

644
00:37:20,270 --> 00:37:21,940
We wouldn't have met
if I didn't run the store.

645
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:24,310
And without you,
the store wouldn't have done so well.

646
00:37:25,310 --> 00:37:28,140
So to sum it up, you and I were

647
00:37:28,310 --> 00:37:32,550
able to do that
thanks to the convenience store.

648
00:37:34,480 --> 00:37:35,680
Grapes.

649
00:37:39,050 --> 00:37:41,490
My gosh, you're so childish. Strawberry!

650
00:37:41,560 --> 00:37:44,060
No, don't say that!
Let's just go with grapes.

651
00:37:44,430 --> 00:37:47,600
-Come on inside.
-You need to take your shoes off.

652
00:37:47,660 --> 00:37:49,160
-Okay.
-Careful.

653
00:37:49,230 --> 00:37:50,360
Mrs. Gong.

654
00:37:50,430 --> 00:37:52,330
This is our house, Yeon-joo.

655
00:37:53,870 --> 00:37:56,600
-Come inside. Let's drink some more.
-What's going on? Hey, Mom.

656
00:37:56,770 --> 00:37:58,570
-What...
-Hey, Dae-hyun.

657
00:37:58,910 --> 00:38:01,440
I called her for something,
and we ended up drinking together.

658
00:38:01,540 --> 00:38:03,480
-Can you take this?
-Oh, okay.

659
00:38:03,640 --> 00:38:06,310
My goodness. Come here, my son.

660
00:38:06,380 --> 00:38:09,550
Dae-hyun, you're such a kind son.

661
00:38:09,620 --> 00:38:10,990
You're the best.

662
00:38:11,050 --> 00:38:13,390
Mom, why did you drink so much?

663
00:38:13,450 --> 00:38:17,830
I was in a good mood today,
so I had a few drinks.

664
00:38:17,890 --> 00:38:21,800
My son made my dream come true.

665
00:38:21,860 --> 00:38:25,270
Your salary is over 100,000 won,
and you're an executive at a big firm.

666
00:38:25,330 --> 00:38:28,640
♫ You have no idea how happy I am ♫

667
00:38:28,700 --> 00:38:31,210
♫ You have no idea how happy I am ♫

668
00:38:31,270 --> 00:38:34,010
Dae-hyun, listen to me.

669
00:38:34,080 --> 00:38:36,240
I don't need a husband.

670
00:38:36,310 --> 00:38:38,880
And I don't need any friends.

671
00:38:38,950 --> 00:38:40,310
All I need is you.

672
00:38:40,380 --> 00:38:43,550
All I need is my son, okay?

673
00:38:43,620 --> 00:38:45,950
-Mom, are you okay?
-Why wouldn't I be okay?

674
00:38:46,020 --> 00:38:50,060
Dae-hyun, I came home
in a really nice car.

675
00:38:50,120 --> 00:38:51,990
Yeon-joo, gave me a ride. Hey, Yeon-joo.

676
00:38:52,060 --> 00:38:54,000
Yes, I'm right here.

677
00:38:54,060 --> 00:38:58,730
My goodness gracious.
Yeon-joo, thank you so much.

678
00:39:00,270 --> 00:39:05,070
Yeon-joo, thank you so much
for drinking with me today.

679
00:39:05,140 --> 00:39:08,680
No, I should be the one to thank you.
You should call me often from now on.

680
00:39:08,740 --> 00:39:10,010
Okay, sure.

681
00:39:10,080 --> 00:39:14,050
Dae-hyun, I owe her a lot.
She did so much for me today.

682
00:39:14,120 --> 00:39:17,280
Now, you should go and take her home.

683
00:39:17,350 --> 00:39:20,320
Escort her to her house. Hurry.

684
00:39:20,390 --> 00:39:21,560
Ma'am, I'll be off now.

685
00:39:21,620 --> 00:39:24,430
Yeon-joo. Goodbye, Yeon-joo.

686
00:39:24,490 --> 00:39:26,030
-I'll see you again.
-Okay.

687
00:39:26,090 --> 00:39:27,190
Bye.

688
00:39:28,260 --> 00:39:30,200
Okay, bye.

689
00:39:34,300 --> 00:39:36,540
Ma'am, you should lie down.

690
00:39:37,140 --> 00:39:40,780
-There you go.
-Okay.

691
00:39:43,280 --> 00:39:46,680
Ma'am, it's time for me to work
at the convenience store.

692
00:39:47,250 --> 00:39:50,180
You should teach Mr. Choi a big lesson
once he comes home.

693
00:39:50,280 --> 00:39:52,620
Okay. Yeon-joo.

694
00:39:52,890 --> 00:39:55,590
Yeon-joo, thank you so much.

695
00:39:55,960 --> 00:40:00,900
I hope you do your best
to help Dae-hyun out.

696
00:40:01,300 --> 00:40:03,930
I never got to live the life I wanted.

697
00:40:04,170 --> 00:40:08,900
But I want Dae-hyun to live differently.

698
00:40:09,170 --> 00:40:11,510
That's my dream.

699
00:40:12,170 --> 00:40:15,080
Okay, Yeon-joo? Please do me a favor.

700
00:40:19,650 --> 00:40:23,250
Thank you. Thank you, Yeon-joo.

701
00:40:48,340 --> 00:40:49,740
-Dae-hyun.
-Yes?

702
00:40:49,810 --> 00:40:51,010
About yesterday...

703
00:40:53,950 --> 00:40:54,950
Well...

704
00:40:56,520 --> 00:40:58,790
Yeon-joo told me

705
00:40:58,920 --> 00:41:02,890
that she wants to apologize,
but apparently, you won't let her.

706
00:41:05,790 --> 00:41:07,530
I'm sure Yeon-joo worked really hard

707
00:41:07,600 --> 00:41:10,400
to make the company
take over our convenience store.

708
00:41:10,460 --> 00:41:12,830
She also took good care of me yesterday.

709
00:41:13,470 --> 00:41:15,640
You should meet up with her

710
00:41:15,740 --> 00:41:18,570
and let her apologize.

711
00:41:18,710 --> 00:41:21,480
And thank her for what she did.

712
00:41:21,680 --> 00:41:23,880
-Mom.
-It's best to get that kind of stuff done

713
00:41:23,940 --> 00:41:25,010
as fast as possible.

714
00:41:25,080 --> 00:41:27,010
You should meet her today
if you have time.

715
00:41:27,280 --> 00:41:28,850
I have dinner plans today.

716
00:41:30,480 --> 00:41:33,690
I'm totally fine.
You should listen to your mother.

717
00:41:36,720 --> 00:41:40,530
He promised to treat me to a nice meal
to cheer me on

718
00:41:40,590 --> 00:41:43,830
saying he feels a bit sad
to let go of the store.

719
00:41:44,060 --> 00:41:45,130
Saet-byul.

720
00:41:46,300 --> 00:41:47,370
It's okay.

721
00:41:47,430 --> 00:41:48,740
Yes, do as I tell you.

722
00:41:48,800 --> 00:41:52,140
You should meet her today, Dae-hyun.

723
00:41:55,280 --> 00:41:57,210
-Mr. Choi.
-Hey.

724
00:41:57,510 --> 00:41:59,810
-Here.
-What's this?

725
00:41:59,880 --> 00:42:01,980
You should give this to Mrs. Gong.

726
00:42:02,050 --> 00:42:05,850
They're white tulips,
and they symbolize "Forgiveness".

727
00:42:06,950 --> 00:42:09,360
-Saet-byul, thank you.
-No problem.

728
00:42:09,620 --> 00:42:12,560
But I don't know
if the flowers will be enough.

729
00:42:13,590 --> 00:42:15,000
Don't worry.

730
00:42:15,060 --> 00:42:18,400
I have something even better up my sleeve.

731
00:42:18,800 --> 00:42:21,870
"Something even better"? What's that?

732
00:42:26,310 --> 00:42:28,310
[Cashier's check]

733
00:42:26,640 --> 00:42:30,380
I met Jang-mi so I could get this money.

734
00:42:30,610 --> 00:42:32,610
I had no ulterior motive.

735
00:42:34,150 --> 00:42:38,190
I told her I run a convenience store,
and that's how she came that day.

736
00:42:38,250 --> 00:42:41,490
You told me you didn't want to see her.

737
00:42:41,560 --> 00:42:45,190
That's why I told her
that I don't know you. That's all.

738
00:42:45,490 --> 00:42:48,100
I'm serious. Please believe me.

739
00:42:55,240 --> 00:42:59,410
These tulips symbolize "Forgiveness".
Saet-byul--

740
00:42:59,470 --> 00:43:00,670
Get them away from me!

741
00:43:01,810 --> 00:43:04,580
Why did you want to go to Zhangjiajie?

742
00:43:06,510 --> 00:43:08,520
Tell me why.

743
00:43:08,720 --> 00:43:11,990
Why don't you just hit me?

744
00:43:14,120 --> 00:43:17,690
Hit me until you feel better.

745
00:43:19,190 --> 00:43:22,430
Forget it. Take this,

746
00:43:22,500 --> 00:43:26,070
go to Zhangjiajie, and get married to her.

747
00:43:26,570 --> 00:43:27,840
Just leave.

748
00:43:30,870 --> 00:43:33,440
Boon-hee, I deserve to die.

749
00:43:39,150 --> 00:43:40,250
You

750
00:43:41,280 --> 00:43:44,850
don't even deserve a beating.

751
00:43:45,650 --> 00:43:47,450
Take all this and get lost.

752
00:43:48,660 --> 00:43:49,820
No, I won't leave.

753
00:43:49,890 --> 00:43:53,630
I'm going to live and die right here.

754
00:43:53,730 --> 00:43:55,360
-Is that so?
-Yes.

755
00:43:55,430 --> 00:43:57,230
Then I'll leave.

756
00:43:57,300 --> 00:43:58,570
Boon-hee!

757
00:44:00,230 --> 00:44:02,770
-Let me go.
-No, I can't.

758
00:44:11,010 --> 00:44:12,880
Boon-hee.

759
00:44:14,680 --> 00:44:16,550
Would you like another cup of coffee?

760
00:44:17,650 --> 00:44:19,220
No, I'll be leaving soon.

761
00:44:19,290 --> 00:44:21,060
-Then should I throw this away?
-Yes.

762
00:44:21,120 --> 00:44:23,260
Okay. Thank you.

763
00:44:30,530 --> 00:44:31,530
Boon-hee.

764
00:44:36,970 --> 00:44:40,470
Boon-hee, I really wanted to see you
before I left.

765
00:44:40,540 --> 00:44:42,340
I'm so glad I got to see you like this.

766
00:44:45,250 --> 00:44:47,780
Life must be really easy for you.

767
00:44:48,550 --> 00:44:50,150
You come and go

768
00:44:50,220 --> 00:44:52,890
whenever you want. What a life.

769
00:44:52,950 --> 00:44:55,560
Back then, I had a reason.

770
00:44:55,990 --> 00:44:58,690
-To be honest--
-I don't want to hear it.

771
00:45:01,030 --> 00:45:03,600
You told me you wanted to see me
before you left.

772
00:45:04,370 --> 00:45:06,000
Well, you saw me, so leave.

773
00:45:11,000 --> 00:45:14,710
Here. Please read it.

774
00:45:17,010 --> 00:45:18,580
I'll be off now.

775
00:45:20,650 --> 00:45:23,750
Boon-hee, I hope you stay well.

776
00:45:41,600 --> 00:45:44,640
[To Gong Boon-hee]

777
00:45:47,510 --> 00:45:48,540
Eat up.

778
00:45:50,310 --> 00:45:53,580
Thank you for asking me
to eat dinner with you today.

779
00:45:54,380 --> 00:45:57,480
No, I'm more grateful
for what you did for my mother yesterday.

780
00:46:02,090 --> 00:46:06,190
I'd like to sincerely apologize
for how rude my mother was to you

781
00:46:06,260 --> 00:46:08,260
in the past.

782
00:46:09,000 --> 00:46:10,930
I've always wanted to apologize for that.

783
00:46:12,570 --> 00:46:15,570
Didn't you tell me
it was a misunderstanding back then?

784
00:46:16,700 --> 00:46:19,340
As I talked to your mother last night,

785
00:46:19,410 --> 00:46:22,240
I got to find out
that she's a great person.

786
00:46:23,380 --> 00:46:25,650
I don't want to avoid it
saying I didn't know anything.

787
00:46:26,410 --> 00:46:29,920
Now that you're being honest about it,
I'll accept your apology.

788
00:46:34,690 --> 00:46:37,460
We promised to be honest
to each other about everything,

789
00:46:38,060 --> 00:46:39,730
but I failed to do that.

790
00:46:40,460 --> 00:46:41,730
From now on,

791
00:46:42,860 --> 00:46:45,430
I'd like to treat you
with my utmost sincerity.

792
00:46:45,500 --> 00:46:46,370
No.

793
00:46:46,730 --> 00:46:51,410
I just want us to remain
as good colleagues.

794
00:47:02,450 --> 00:47:03,580
[Dear Boon-hee,]

795
00:47:04,520 --> 00:47:07,820
[I'm leaving for China tonight.]

796
00:47:08,760 --> 00:47:11,760
[Hong Jang-mi]

797
00:47:09,190 --> 00:47:10,960
[I'm sorry for not telling you
in advance.]

798
00:47:12,190 --> 00:47:15,230
[I'm in love with someone.]

799
00:47:16,260 --> 00:47:18,270
[I know I shouldn't do this
to my parents,]

800
00:47:18,470 --> 00:47:21,240
[but I believe they'll forgive me
in the future]

801
00:47:21,300 --> 00:47:23,170
[once they see me happily married.]

802
00:47:24,470 --> 00:47:28,980
[Boon-hee, I know you probably hate me
for disappearing without a word.]

803
00:47:29,540 --> 00:47:32,650
[But I trust that you'll understand.]

804
00:47:32,480 --> 00:47:33,650
[From Hong Jang-mi]

805
00:47:33,650 --> 00:47:35,880
[I hope you reply
once you're no longer angry at me.]

806
00:47:36,320 --> 00:47:38,290
[International Departures]

807
00:47:41,720 --> 00:47:43,860
[I will always be waiting.]

808
00:47:44,930 --> 00:47:47,230
[From your everlasting friend, Jang-mi.]

809
00:47:50,930 --> 00:47:54,270
[P.S. The photo inside the envelope]

810
00:47:54,370 --> 00:47:56,940
[is the photo we took last time
at the school picnic.]

811
00:47:57,540 --> 00:47:58,670
My goodness.

812
00:48:00,540 --> 00:48:02,380
I can't believe I used to be so young.

813
00:48:09,520 --> 00:48:11,650
Boon-hee.

814
00:48:14,020 --> 00:48:16,260
I'm sorry for living such a lousy life.

815
00:48:31,040 --> 00:48:33,610
He's coming. He's coming.

816
00:48:39,650 --> 00:48:40,810
Welcome.

817
00:48:41,380 --> 00:48:43,650
-Saet-byul.
-Mr. Choi.

818
00:48:44,020 --> 00:48:47,450
No, wait. Take a few steps back. Go on.

819
00:48:47,550 --> 00:48:49,060
A bit more.

820
00:48:49,560 --> 00:48:51,890
Now, let me disinfect myself.

821
00:48:58,230 --> 00:49:00,070
Okay, all done. It's perfect.

822
00:49:00,670 --> 00:49:03,700
I'm done disinfecting myself.
I'm totally clean now.

823
00:49:03,770 --> 00:49:05,910
The ex-girlfriend virus is gone.
There's none of that.

824
00:49:06,270 --> 00:49:09,010
Mr. Choi, you forgot one thing.

825
00:49:09,080 --> 00:49:10,280
Give me your hands.

826
00:49:10,740 --> 00:49:12,880
Gosh, you're a perfectionist.

827
00:49:15,180 --> 00:49:17,250
-Okay.
-It's best to do things perfectly.

828
00:49:18,290 --> 00:49:19,350
All done.

829
00:49:19,690 --> 00:49:21,150
You came really early.

830
00:49:21,220 --> 00:49:23,420
I came running because I missed you.

831
00:49:23,960 --> 00:49:25,030
Good job.

832
00:49:25,730 --> 00:49:26,860
My dad will be here soon,

833
00:49:26,930 --> 00:49:29,100
so let's go home together once he arrives.

834
00:49:32,200 --> 00:49:33,330
-Sir!
-Dad!

835
00:49:36,340 --> 00:49:38,610
-We're home.
-We're home.

836
00:49:39,910 --> 00:49:41,880
-What did you eat?
-What do you mean?

837
00:49:42,140 --> 00:49:43,910
Did you eat something nice with Yeon-joo?

838
00:49:43,980 --> 00:49:45,380
What did you eat with her?

839
00:49:46,250 --> 00:49:48,120
We had meat.

840
00:49:48,320 --> 00:49:50,380
You bought her beef, right?

841
00:49:50,820 --> 00:49:54,520
Yeon-joo is very classy,
so it's better to buy her beef.

842
00:49:54,720 --> 00:49:57,590
-From now on, keep that in mind.
-Gosh, forget it.

843
00:49:58,230 --> 00:49:59,830
Dae-hyun, I noticed yesterday

844
00:49:59,890 --> 00:50:02,560
that Yeon-joo is very considerate
and warm-hearted.

845
00:50:03,230 --> 00:50:05,900
I did what you asked.
I accepted her apology and thanked her.

846
00:50:05,970 --> 00:50:07,330
So that's enough.

847
00:50:07,400 --> 00:50:10,700
It seems like Yeon-joo thinks of you
very differently now.

848
00:50:11,000 --> 00:50:13,040
She's not like how she used to be.

849
00:50:15,040 --> 00:50:16,510
Mom, please stop.

850
00:50:18,310 --> 00:50:19,380
What?

851
00:50:20,450 --> 00:50:22,550
I'll go upstairs.

852
00:50:31,060 --> 00:50:34,130
Mom, will you stop talking to me
about Yeon-joo?

853
00:50:36,460 --> 00:50:37,500
Why?

854
00:50:38,230 --> 00:50:39,330
Why can't I talk about her?

855
00:50:39,400 --> 00:50:41,800
What do you mean?
I broke up with her. It's over.

856
00:50:42,400 --> 00:50:45,670
And did you already forget
about what happened in the past?

857
00:50:45,940 --> 00:50:47,170
How could I forget?

858
00:50:48,010 --> 00:50:49,340
How could I ever forget that?

859
00:50:49,410 --> 00:50:52,110
How could I forget the incident
that helped me become the insurance queen?

860
00:50:52,180 --> 00:50:54,380
Why would you remember it like that?

861
00:50:54,450 --> 00:50:57,480
Then how do you want me to remember it?

862
00:50:57,820 --> 00:51:00,390
Do you think she was the first person
to treat me like that?

863
00:51:01,220 --> 00:51:03,390
That could sometimes lead
to good relationships.

864
00:51:03,460 --> 00:51:04,930
That's life.

865
00:51:04,990 --> 00:51:06,790
What do you want?
Should I get back with her?

866
00:51:06,860 --> 00:51:08,100
Is that what you want?

867
00:51:08,560 --> 00:51:10,660
Yes. If that happens,
I'd ask for nothing more.

868
00:51:10,730 --> 00:51:12,370
I'll even dance to celebrate.

869
00:51:12,970 --> 00:51:14,530
What's the matter with you?

870
00:51:17,040 --> 00:51:18,740
Do you think I'm doing this for myself?

871
00:51:19,040 --> 00:51:21,740
I'm doing this for you.

872
00:51:22,540 --> 00:51:25,710
I'm not telling you to get back with her
for no reason.

873
00:51:25,880 --> 00:51:28,920
I could tell that she really wants
to get back with you yesterday.

874
00:51:29,380 --> 00:51:33,150
I don't think you'll get dragged around
like you did before.

875
00:51:33,250 --> 00:51:36,290
And I feel like her family
will treat you with more respect.

876
00:51:36,360 --> 00:51:37,820
Gosh, if you like her that much,

877
00:51:39,590 --> 00:51:41,900
why don't you go live with her instead?

878
00:52:33,050 --> 00:52:34,580
Dad, I'll be off now.

879
00:52:34,950 --> 00:52:36,180
Aren't you going to eat?

880
00:52:36,250 --> 00:52:38,550
No, I'm not that hungry.

881
00:52:38,620 --> 00:52:41,150
-At least have some soup,
-No, it's okay.

882
00:52:42,160 --> 00:52:43,260
I'll be off now.

883
00:52:45,860 --> 00:52:47,060
-See you.
-Bye.

884
00:52:53,730 --> 00:52:56,440
-Ma'am, have some breakfast.
-I told you to get lost.

885
00:52:58,540 --> 00:53:00,040
I'm not kidding. Close the door.

886
00:53:04,480 --> 00:53:07,180
My gosh, what's with the mood?

887
00:53:12,950 --> 00:53:14,590
[Grab the opportunity.
From Store Manager Bae Geun-sik]

888
00:53:16,460 --> 00:53:18,960
[Lifestyle Platform, GS25]

889
00:53:17,290 --> 00:53:18,630
-Let's put it here.
-Okay.

890
00:53:19,630 --> 00:53:21,090
Why would you bring this outside?

891
00:53:21,160 --> 00:53:22,730
What's this doing in the storage?

892
00:53:22,930 --> 00:53:26,170
Mr. Choi left it there for me.

893
00:53:26,230 --> 00:53:28,100
I'm the manager now.

894
00:53:28,340 --> 00:53:30,000
By the way, I checked the POS machine.

895
00:53:30,070 --> 00:53:32,340
And I noticed that you guys ran the place
like a pop-up store.

896
00:53:32,410 --> 00:53:34,940
I want you to forget
everything you learned.

897
00:53:35,740 --> 00:53:37,810
-What?
-New wine belongs in a new bottle.

898
00:53:38,710 --> 00:53:40,350
I used to serve
in the special forces unit.

899
00:53:41,110 --> 00:53:42,280
This is too big.

900
00:53:42,350 --> 00:53:44,050
We'll have to call the district office
to throw it away.

901
00:53:44,550 --> 00:53:46,920
Say hello. She's Kyung-hee,
an expert in this business.

902
00:53:48,820 --> 00:53:51,120
-Hi, I'm Jung Saet-byul.
-I'm Park Kyung-hee.

903
00:53:50,020 --> 00:53:53,390
[Crispy chicken fried with fresh oil]

904
00:53:52,030 --> 00:53:54,230
You're a lot younger than expected.

905
00:53:54,660 --> 00:53:55,830
What year did you enter college?

906
00:53:57,100 --> 00:53:58,470
You're like a rude customer.

907
00:53:59,200 --> 00:54:00,230
What?

908
00:54:01,300 --> 00:54:03,670
You obviously know I didn't go to college.

909
00:54:03,740 --> 00:54:05,370
I didn't even graduate high school.

910
00:54:07,140 --> 00:54:08,940
Kyung-hee worked out for a long time.

911
00:54:09,010 --> 00:54:10,340
You did Muay Thai and what else?

912
00:54:10,410 --> 00:54:12,450
Kendo. Second-degree black belt.

913
00:54:13,080 --> 00:54:14,650
Oh, I see.

914
00:54:16,250 --> 00:54:17,420
I hope we get along.

915
00:54:34,230 --> 00:54:36,270
I advise you to use this strength
for work.

916
00:54:37,240 --> 00:54:38,510
We have tons of stuff to do.

917
00:54:40,270 --> 00:54:43,140
[Lifestyle Platform, GS25]

918
00:54:43,210 --> 00:54:44,380
She's not an easy one.

919
00:54:44,440 --> 00:54:45,350
[Crispy chicken fried with fresh oil]

920
00:54:45,410 --> 00:54:46,410
This is interesting.

921
00:54:50,580 --> 00:54:51,720
It's 2,000 won.

922
00:55:04,060 --> 00:55:05,170
Assistant Manager.

923
00:55:05,870 --> 00:55:08,500
When you run a convenience store,
how you display the items is very crucial.

924
00:55:08,570 --> 00:55:10,900
But the way things are displayed here

925
00:55:10,970 --> 00:55:12,710
is a complete mess.

926
00:55:15,180 --> 00:55:16,010
So what's your point?

927
00:55:16,080 --> 00:55:18,080
What do you think?
I want you to redisplay them.

928
00:55:20,410 --> 00:55:23,420
-Sir, we'll return to the head office.
-Bye.

929
00:55:23,550 --> 00:55:25,190
-Good work, today.
-Good work.

930
00:55:25,250 --> 00:55:26,150
Have a good day.

931
00:55:27,550 --> 00:55:28,490
Store Manager.

932
00:55:28,560 --> 00:55:30,560
-Yes?
-What's our new item?

933
00:55:30,620 --> 00:55:32,130
We have something amazing in the fridge.

934
00:55:32,190 --> 00:55:34,360
Really? Let's go and check. Come on.

935
00:56:00,820 --> 00:56:04,060
Let me help you with your studies.

936
00:56:08,760 --> 00:56:10,430
[Mr. Choi is watching you.
You can do this!]

937
00:57:05,190 --> 00:57:06,790
Mr. Choi, it's time for me
to get off work.

938
00:57:07,120 --> 00:57:08,660
Okay, Saet-byul. You did great.

939
00:57:24,140 --> 00:57:25,640
I'm home.

940
00:57:27,410 --> 00:57:28,440
Mrs. Gong.

941
00:57:37,220 --> 00:57:38,350
I'm home.

942
00:57:39,350 --> 00:57:40,490
Hey.

943
00:57:41,620 --> 00:57:43,590
Did you eat?

944
00:57:46,490 --> 00:57:48,290
My goodness.

945
00:57:49,560 --> 00:57:51,600
I don't have an appetite.

946
00:57:52,630 --> 00:57:54,200
I'm not hungry at all.

947
00:57:58,440 --> 00:57:59,610
Saet-byul.

948
00:58:00,640 --> 00:58:05,010
What did I do so wrong?

949
00:58:06,910 --> 00:58:11,320
Dae-hyun has never
yelled at me like that before.

950
00:58:16,690 --> 00:58:19,660
Saet-byul, listen.

951
00:58:20,360 --> 00:58:22,130
Do you know

952
00:58:22,200 --> 00:58:25,370
what it is that scares me the most?

953
00:58:26,730 --> 00:58:30,140
It's the possibility
that my child might end up

954
00:58:30,840 --> 00:58:34,340
living a difficult and poor life
just like me.

955
00:58:34,410 --> 00:58:36,340
That scares me the most.

956
00:58:37,680 --> 00:58:41,280
That's why I said all those stuff.

957
00:58:41,350 --> 00:58:45,050
I still can't believe
he yelled at me like that.

958
00:58:46,620 --> 00:58:47,920
I mean, it's not like

959
00:58:49,090 --> 00:58:52,530
I have a rich husband.

960
00:58:58,400 --> 00:58:59,500
And...

961
00:59:02,840 --> 00:59:06,610
And it's not like I have
a lot of money saved up.

962
00:59:06,670 --> 00:59:09,380
The only person I can rely on

963
00:59:09,440 --> 00:59:13,250
is my son, Dae-hyun.

964
00:59:22,120 --> 00:59:25,790
Ma'am, don't worry too much.

965
00:59:28,900 --> 00:59:31,400
I'm sure he's regretting it right now.

966
00:59:46,680 --> 00:59:49,680
Saet-byul, are you sure
this sausage stew will do?

967
00:59:49,820 --> 00:59:52,650
Why didn't you pick something better?
I wanted to buy you something delicious.

968
00:59:52,720 --> 00:59:55,790
What are you talking about?
I love sausage stew.

969
00:59:56,520 --> 00:59:57,590
It looks so delicious.

970
00:59:58,990 --> 01:00:01,890
-My gosh, you... I can't believe this.
-What's wrong?

971
01:00:01,960 --> 01:00:05,730
You just... Gosh, you really know
how to eat your sausage stew.

972
01:00:06,130 --> 01:00:08,740
-What?
-I'm talking about the instant noodles.

973
01:00:10,300 --> 01:00:12,570
Instant noodles are a must
when you eat sausage stew.

974
01:00:12,640 --> 01:00:14,070
Who doesn't add instant noodles?

975
01:00:14,140 --> 01:00:16,140
-Some people don't.
-Are you serious?

976
01:00:16,210 --> 01:00:18,680
Yes. It gives me the creeps.

977
01:00:18,750 --> 01:00:20,780
-That's a big mistake.
-I know, right?

978
01:00:20,980 --> 01:00:23,120
It's like cooking kimchi stew
without kimchi.

979
01:00:23,180 --> 01:00:24,920
It's like doenjang stew without doenjang.

980
01:00:24,980 --> 01:00:26,420
And gochujang stew without gochujang.

981
01:00:26,490 --> 01:00:29,490
Yes, exactly.
It's like sundae soup with no sundae.

982
01:00:31,060 --> 01:00:32,830
How was work today?

983
01:00:33,930 --> 01:00:36,330
It's still the same store,
so it was pretty much the same.

984
01:00:37,500 --> 01:00:38,630
I'm relieved to hear that.

985
01:00:39,870 --> 01:00:43,670
Saet-byul, the instant noodles
are starting to cook,

986
01:00:44,270 --> 01:00:47,440
and it's kind of getting me excited.
What do you think I should do?

987
01:00:48,040 --> 01:00:49,780
-It's time to take them out.
-Exactly.

988
01:01:06,730 --> 01:01:08,260
-Mr. Choi.
-Yes?

989
01:01:12,130 --> 01:01:13,970
You should apologize to your mother.

990
01:01:19,440 --> 01:01:22,910
You shouldn't have
yelled at her like that yesterday.

991
01:01:23,980 --> 01:01:27,650
Saet-byul, I always listen to my mother.

992
01:01:29,580 --> 01:01:30,650
But last night was different.

993
01:01:32,420 --> 01:01:35,590
Don't be like that.
You're usually not like this.

994
01:01:37,460 --> 01:01:40,190
Saet-byul,
about what my mom said yesterday...

995
01:01:40,260 --> 01:01:43,460
Don't take it to heart, okay?

996
01:01:48,900 --> 01:01:49,970
Let's eat.

997
01:01:58,580 --> 01:02:02,350
[Mr. Choi, I don't want you to change.]

998
01:02:03,220 --> 01:02:05,720
[I want you to remain as a kind son.]

999
01:02:06,220 --> 01:02:08,690
[And I want you to continue
to do your best with work.]

1000
01:02:09,960 --> 01:02:12,460
[If you were your normal self,
you wouldn't have fought with your mom.]

1001
01:02:12,530 --> 01:02:14,790
[You would've just said "Okay, Mom"
and ended the conversation.]

1002
01:02:16,700 --> 01:02:18,260
Eat up, Saet-byul.

1003
01:02:19,670 --> 01:02:21,170
[If it weren't for me...]

1004
01:02:22,370 --> 01:02:23,770
[If I wasn't around...]

1005
01:02:25,140 --> 01:02:27,670
[Because that's the kind of person
you normally are.]

1006
01:02:29,110 --> 01:02:31,510
Hurry up and eat.
I might finish everything.

1007
01:02:53,670 --> 01:02:56,800
[I will never be able to find a room
that's as cozy and warm]

1008
01:02:56,870 --> 01:02:58,570
[as this one.]

1009
01:03:26,170 --> 01:03:28,840
[Mrs. Gong, thank you.]

1010
01:03:30,470 --> 01:03:32,540
[You're such a great person.]

1011
01:03:32,840 --> 01:03:36,110
[And I don't want to be the one
who makes you feel scared.]

1012
01:03:37,010 --> 01:03:39,780
[And sir, thank you so much
for everything.]

1013
01:04:11,380 --> 01:04:14,380
[Mr. Choi, when you told me
that you like me,]

1014
01:04:15,010 --> 01:04:17,320
[I felt happy and anxious
at the same time]

1015
01:04:18,620 --> 01:04:20,590
[because deep down inside,]

1016
01:04:21,050 --> 01:04:23,290
[I knew that things might end this way.]

1017
01:04:25,290 --> 01:04:28,230
[Although it didn't last long,
I will never forget]

1018
01:04:29,160 --> 01:04:30,500
[how happy you made me feel.]

1019
01:04:31,760 --> 01:04:34,370
[Thank you, Mr. Choi.]
